ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: A very broad look at a lot of nanomaterial applications but, given the student-led nature of the course, you could really personalize the topics/direction of the course. The project was a really fun-- although challenging!-- way to integrate classroom academic knowledge into hands on skills development/relation to current research. Would definitely recommend!
Sure. I will recommend to people who is interested in nano world. Especially people with certain research background.
I would highly recommend this course to anyone who is synthesizing nanomaterials as a part of their research.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: Very helpful for developing background knowledge for dissertation work--- allowed me to see other potential platforms for my current research (as well as learn more about reading journal articles with a more critical eye).
Yes this is very informative course.
I got plenty of knowledge on nano syntheses in bio-areas, especially surface doping or functionalization of carbon materials.
Lots of new subjects in nanotechnology I was exposed to
